\begin_layout Standard
For a robot to operate autonomously, it must rely on efficient algorithms
 to provide a plan of movements given a few conditions or constraints by
 the operator.
 However, developing such an algorithm becomes much more difficult when
 the robot's environment is not well structured and contains many dynamically
 moving obstacles.
 Recent studies have begun to make progress towards safer, autonomous robots
 by combining methodologies from several research areas including, motion
 planning, fault characterization and detection, and mechanical design.
 Specifically research has focused on collision avoidance [ref], ensuring
 safe robot dynamics [ref], and passive and active compliance [ref].
\end_layout

